{
  "bookId": "heshanggong-laozi",
  "num": 26,
  "title": "第二十六章（重德）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "重為輕根，"
    },
    {
      "text": "靜為躁君。"
    },
    {
      "text": "是以聖人終日行，不離輜重。"
    },
    {
      "text": "雖有榮觀，燕處超然。"
    },
    {
      "text": "奈何萬乘之主"
    },
    {
      "text": "而以身輕天下？"
    },
    {
      "text": "輕則失臣，"
    },
    {
      "text": "躁則失君。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人君不重則不尊，治身不重則失神，草木之花葉輕，故零落，根重故長存也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人君不靜則失威，治身不靜則身危，龍靜故能變化，虎躁故夭虧也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "輜，靜也。聖人終日行道，不離其靜與重也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "榮觀，謂宮闕。燕處，后妃所居也。超然，遠避而不處也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "奈何者，疾時主傷痛之辭。萬乘之主謂，王者。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "王者至尊，而以其身行輕躁乎。疾時王奢恣輕淫也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "王者輕淫則失其臣，治身輕淫則失其精。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "王者行躁疾則失其君位，治身躁疾則失其精神也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
